China Aims to Have 284 GW of Hydro Capacity by 2015, CEC Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-22T07:15:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/china-aims-to-have-284-gw-of-hydro-capacity-by-2015-cec-says.html
China aims to increase its
hydropower output capacity to 284 gigawatts by 2015 and to 330
gigawatts by 2020, said Ouyang Changyu, deputy secretary at the
China Electricity Council.   The country will focus on building six hydro bases along
western rivers including Jinsha River, Nu River, Dadu River and
Lancang River, Ouyang said at a conference in Beijing today.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Ying Wang in Beijing at 
 ywang30@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ryan Woo at 
 rwoo5@bloomberg.net  